==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Openbill
<hw>O"pen*bill`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A bird of the genus <gen>Anastomus</gen>, allied to the stork; --
so called because the two parts of the bill touch only at the base and
tip. One species inhabits India, another Africa. Called also
<altname>open-beak</altname>. See <xex>Illust.</xex> <sd>(m)</sd>, under
<er>Beak</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

